body:
> Also, the travis tests are calling ./ci/code_checks.sh with no parameters so nothing is happening there.

@JustinZhengBC : Actually that's not the case.  We set `LINT=1` for the build's environment configuration.  That being said, your point is well taken, and I think it goes along the lines of the fact that we need a separate script for contributors to sanity-check their code for style errors.

@datapythonista : I don't remember which issue had the discussion about adding a contributor-specific style check script.  If there is one, I think this issue would certainly be a good argument for having one.
